This paper deals with influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically focuses on the study of social networks and their properties. The paper also involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical applications of influence maximization, which could place it under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
